Description.LocalizedString: A crown emanating a festive and ominous aura created by The Entity’s biggest fan.

A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.
“Thank you for supporting & inspiring us along the years!” —The Dead by Daylight Team

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Sharp, protuberant fibula, inflamed by excessive lymph.

Description.LocalizedString: A pair of comfortable jeans for searching and executing any distressed visitor.
He knew these jeans would be sturdy enough for physical labor of all kinds.
You can't catch a rabbit without getting your hands, and pants, dirty.
Cool down and show off those calves with tastefully mangled 3/4 pants.
Cool down and show off those calves with tastefully mangled 3/4 pants.
At midnight, he lit up his creation and a wall of fire engulfed him.
A farmboy’s attire, festooned with the stripped skin of a Coldwind Farm pig. A terrifying sight that could give pause to any sheriff’s in his way.
The result of chasing countless victims through thorny bushes and farmland.
There’s something friendly and warm about this uniform. Surely, you can trust anyone wearing it...
Despite the quality of the work, the pants ripped with the first attack.
Max kneeled in front of the screen, listening like the feline was talking to him personally.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: These dirt-lined jeans are a new addition. They smell of cheap cologne and something else…perhaps rotten flesh.

Description.LocalizedString: A pair of bloodstained jeans that don’t smell that bad because of the cold.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: These ruined jeans are the opposite of fine clothing.

Immerse yourself in the wilderness. Live off the land. Become one with nature. Devour some fresh roadkill. Drink your own urine (if necessary). The classic outfit of a true frontier survivalist!
These filthy slacks loosely resemble part of a uniform of sorts. They appear to be covered in dark stains. Could be grease… or dried blood.

Description.LocalizedString: Pants reinforced with added material and complimented with an eye-catching belt buckle. They held up well during a murderous chase through thorny brush.
Canvas pants favored by workers for being tough, these won’t tear even if they’re brushed by, for example, a shotgun covered in rusty nails.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Dark pair of eyes, peering through a thick film of yellow secretions.

Description.LocalizedString: Broad-brimmed hat and a decorated shirt to scout the woodlands for new victims. Includes badges for Fire Safety, Woodland Management, and Knot Tying. FYI, a noose counts as a knot.
He tore one of the sleeves while putting on the shirt.
Thick cotton soaks up any fat stains, while the bandolier holds whiskey and hot sauce for basting, and tasting.
The Hawaiian shirt frames an impressively char-grilled figure. Mmm... something smells good.
The Hawaiian shirt frames an impressively char-grilled figure. Mmm... something smells good.
He gathered all kinds of tools to tinker a metallic frame for the pyre he planned to build.
Even his parents’ prize-winning pig suffered his wrath, a stinking trophy to be adorned upon his head.
Stretched skin stitched from the shreds of his victims.
A beacon of American wholesomeness, right up there with apple pie.
A mask he found himself wearing at the masquerade ball.
Singing and smiling, the tv cat was never bothered by his appearance.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: What’s left of the tank top you wanted.
What’s left of the tank top you wanted.

Description.LocalizedString: He spent the entire winter ridding Coldwind Farm of anything that moved.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Twisted, crooked skin covered with the badly torn remains of a victim's undershirt.

A soft, fuzzy cap made of raccoon skins with a cute tail at the back. It's the inanimate pet you always dreamed of.

Description.LocalizedString: That's a proper mountain man beard too. It will provide much warmth through the winter months.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Don't mind the muttonchops. The cap itself is a suspiciously tight fit.

Description.LocalizedString: The inside of the cap has the word "Buck" written in smudged, black pen.
A tight-fitting jacket clearly made for someone of smaller stature. The inside tag has a name written in sloppy, black marker.
A cozy plaid shirt found amongst his father’s belongings. This top keeps one warm and obscures bloodstains quite effectively.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: A wooden-handle hammer punctured by nails dipped in bile to pummel your prey to a slimy pulp.

Description.LocalizedString: You can find anything you need in the woods, even a sturdy weapon, such as this. Trees harbor a lot of anger, and you can help to let it out.
The club was heavy, and its spikes were as sharp as needles.
Not everyone has the time to craft a club from wood, and that car's just sitting on those blocks…
A hefty chunk of flesh and bone, cooked to perfection and crawling with maggots. Probably the best tasting weapon out there.
He repurposed a broken firework launcher into a weapon to bludgeon sozzled partygoers at the local trailer park.
Sharpened knives, strapped to the metal frame of a sheriff car’s lights. An improvised weapon that demonstrates a proclivity for violence in the maker’s brain.
Both deals a powerful blow and peels off the skin of his victims.
Give them something to cry about with a hammer made of milk bottles.
This hammer was thought to be lost to a beehive out back, but a few stings later, he had a terrifying weapon.
A heavy hammer carved in gold.
The credits rolled as the cat ate from its bowl in the background, not caring for Max anymore.
Buckskin was wrapped around the handle to prevent the hammer from slipping when striking.
A hefty cattle hammer with a festive rodent flair.
The hammer is remarkably clean despite the amount of blood and brains it has spilled.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: A simple shovel. Probably dangerous when used as a weapon. Ya dig?

This weighted pickaxe was once used for chipping away at stone. These days it is used for chipping away at bone.

Description.LocalizedString: Spiked… for your pleasure.

Description.LocalizedString: Come here, my little sausage.
Any frustration over the gun's damaged barrel can be alleviated by bludgeoning the stock into a victim's head.
The business end of this shotgun is wrapped tight in extra flannel torn from his shirt, to keep the fingers warm while gripping cold steel.
This spiked hammer combines rusty BBQ tools from the old Coldwind farmhouse. It offers a crafty way to tenderize even the most venous meat. Waste not, want not.
The hero's eyes always looked kind beneath his mask.
He hoped that one day he could be just like the superhero.
The hero didn’t carry a weapon, which he always found confusing.
The hero’s eyes told him everything would be all right one day.
He knew he would never be able to fly, but he wanted to try anyway.
The hero never carried a weapon, so he saw this as an improvement.
